{"key":"processedPost-6593775","value":{"id":6593775,"first":6593570,"last":6593991,"when":1172089182,"utime":"02/21/07 10:19 PM","cleanedPost":"Cakes should be <i>fully colonized, plus one week</i>, before birthing.  The reason is they won't fruit sooner than that anyway, so leave them in the jars where they're not drying out while the mycelium consolidates its hold on the substrate.<br />If the pink spot is mold, it's probably Geotrichum or similar.  Toss it.  <br />Fine verm is ok to use.  In fact, it will make a better filter on top than course verm.  It does great in the brf as well.<br />RR"}}